  "prompt": "What is the legal history of money laundering prohibitions?",
  "response": "Here's an overview of the legal history of money laundering prohibitions:\n\n1. Early Origins:\n- Informal anti-money laundering efforts date back to ancient civilizations\n- Formal legal frameworks began developing in the 20th century\n\n2. United States Developments:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (1970) - First comprehensive anti-money laundering legislation\n- Required financial institutions to report large cash transactions\n- Established reporting and record-keeping requirements\n\n3. International Developments:\n- 1988 Vienna Convention against drug trafficking\n- 1989 Financial Action Task Force (FATF) established\n- Developed international standards for combating money laundering\n\n4. Key Legislative Milestones:\n- Money Laundering Control Act (1986)\n- Anti-Drug Abuse Act (1988)\n- Annunzio-Wylie Anti-Money Laundering Act (1992)\n- Patriot Act (2001) - Significantly expanded enforcement capabilities\n\n5. Global Expansion:\n- Increasing international cooperation\n- Expanded regulations across financial sectors\n- Enhanced criminal penalties\n- More sophisticated detection mechanisms\n\n6. Modern Era:\n- Increased focus on digital currency and cryptocurrency regulations\n- Sophisticated technological tracking methods\n- Growing international collaboration in enforcement\n\nThis represents a general overview of money laundering prohibition legal history.",
